The paper deals with planning for self-interested agents in multiagent settings, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the problem of scalability in traditional I-POMDPs, which is a common issue in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to modeling agent populations using anonymity and context-specific independence, which could be relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
